HEADWORD: Fomes
<hw>Fo"mes</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"m⟦emac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Fomites</plw>
<pr>(f⟦ocr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*t⟦emac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>fomes</ets>,
<ets>-itis</ets>, touch-wood, tinder.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any
substance supposed to be capable of absorbing, retaining, and
transporting contagious or infectious germs; <as>as, woolen clothes are
said to be active <ex>fomites</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

